In configure view, if I click on the owner field to edit it, then click on the board title, both show as editable

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Server*. Using *JIRA Software Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWCLOUD-5900].
  {panel}

If the description of an issue (or any other field that is being displayed in the card) is too long, the description is cutoff in the 'Print Cards' option.

In the planning board, the field is also cutoff, but differently. The font could  be smaller when printing to display all the content of the card.

Errors in Javascript console:

{code}
An exception has occurred in http://localhost:2990/jira/s/en_UKecn2k2/731/12/6.0.4-SNAPSHOT/_/download/resources/com.pyxis.greenhopper.jira:gh-rapid-common/CreateProjectAndView.js at 260 : Uncaught TypeError: Object [object Object] has no method 'prop' 
{code}

According to the [Creating a Board|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/GH/Creating+a+Board] documentation:

{quote}
Before you begin, please note that you will need the JIRA 'Create Shared Objects' global permission before you can create a board.
{quote}

However, if a user that doesn't have the "Create Shared Objects" permission but has a filter shared with it by someone else, goes to the 'Advanced' tab, this user is able to create a board.
